  "type": "elizaosDailySummary",
  "title": "Daily Report - 2026-05-13",
  "categories": [
    {
      "title": "ElizaOS Community Discussion: V3 Development, Eliza-1 Model Series, and GODL Integration",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "In the general discussion channel, community members exchanged greetings and raised questions about v3 development progress. One member asked for clarification on whether current v3 work is primarily focused on infrastructure stabilization or if the full autonomous agent workflow stack is close to being publicly exposed. They also inquired about the integration status of the new identity and AgentID system in the upcoming architecture. No direct response to these technical questions was recorded in the channel.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
          "posters": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1778723949294-xv9a9v.jpg"
        },
        {
          "text": "A community member shared details about the latest Eliza-1 model series, which is based exclusively on Qwen3.5. The lineup includes models ranging from 0.6B, which is the smallest and capable of running offline on any phone, up to a 27B model with a 1 million token context window. A new 0.8B model is currently being trained on H200 hardware. The series is designed to cover a wide range of hardware targets from mobile phones to servers and workstations.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
          "posters": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1778723983066-1n9zie.png"
        },
        {
          "text": "A warning video was shared in the discussion channel in response to another user, though no additional context about its content was provided in the text of the conversation.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
          "videos": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/elizaos-media/beware_of_20251030_115242_0000-1_686829de.mp4",
          "posters": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1778724006994-0684li.png"
        },
        {
          "text": "The results of an auto.fun AI Sprint competition were shared, announcing the winning teams after weeks of building, community voting, and live demos. First place went to Build4, second place to Clawdyland, with a third place also mentioned.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
          "images": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/elizaos-media/embed-image-1504118889158807753_7a0d13ae.jpg"
        },
        {
          "text": "In the coders channel, a community member working on business development for GODL, a gamified on-chain mining protocol on Solana, reached out to explore potential integration with elizaOS. GODL exposes its system through SDKs, websocket streams, automation hooks, and a public skill.md file designed for agent and tool integrations. The member highlighted potential use cases including autonomous mining and staking strategies, agent-managed wallets, competing mining behaviors, and public leaderboards. Odilitime responded positively, noting that the skill.md file could be used as-is, and agreed to continue the conversation via direct message to avoid bot interference and share further documentation.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1300025221834739744"
        }
      ],
      "topic": "discordrawdata"
    },
